Veteran anchor, Noxolo Grootboom, will be joining the eNCA line-up (screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Veteran news broadcaster Noxolo Grootboom has been awarded another honorary doctorate from the Nelson Mandela University in Qgeberha. READ: Veteran broadcaster Noxolo Grootboom honoured The veteran's first honorary doctorate was given by Rhodes University in 2021. Groootboom retired last year after 37 years in the newsroom. The Nelson Mandela University has awarded Retired SABC isiXhosa news anchor Noxolo Grootboom with an honorary doctorate. It's for her contribution to journalism and for preserving and promoting the isiXhosa language. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/mkg73JaeVE